471
00:25:38,662 --> 00:25:40,498
NO PHYSIOLOGICAL CHANGES.

472
00:25:40,538 --> 00:25:43,209
CAPTAIN...

473
00:25:43,250 --> 00:25:46,837
I DIDN'T BLACK OUT WHEN
MR. JARIS' WIFE WAS KILLED.

474
00:25:49,798 --> 00:25:51,717
ALL RIGHT, SCOTTY,

475
00:25:51,758 --> 00:25:53,760
LET'S HAVE IT.

476
00:25:53,802 --> 00:25:55,804
WE WERE HOLDING HANDS.

477
00:25:55,846 --> 00:25:58,807
WHEN THE LIGHTS WENT OUT,
THE CIRCLE WAS BROKEN.

478
00:25:58,849 --> 00:26:00,726
I HEARD THE POOR LADY
SCREAM, AND I WAS--

479
00:26:00,767 --> 00:26:02,395
I WAS NEAR THE HEAD
OF THE TABLE ANYWAY.

480
00:26:02,436 --> 00:26:04,355
I WENT TOWARD HER, BUT...

481
00:26:04,397 --> 00:26:08,025
THERE WAS...
SOMETHING IN MY WAY.

482
00:26:08,067 --> 00:26:10,861
SOMETHING?
YOU MEAN, SOMEONE.

483
00:26:10,903 --> 00:26:13,864
NO, CAPTAIN, SOME...

484
00:26:13,906 --> 00:26:15,074
THING.

485
00:26:15,115 --> 00:26:18,660
COLD, IT WAS,
LIKE A...

486
00:26:18,702 --> 00:26:20,662
STINKING DRAFT OUT
OF A SLAUGHTERHOUSE,

487
00:26:20,704 --> 00:26:22,706
BUT IT WASN'T R--

488
00:26:22,748 --> 00:26:24,708
REALLY THERE.

489
00:26:24,750 --> 00:26:27,669
LIKE A--

490
00:26:27,711 --> 00:26:30,005
IF YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

491
00:26:30,047 --> 00:26:31,757
COMPUTER?

492
00:26:31,798 --> 00:26:34,801
SUBJECT RELAYING
ACCURATE ACCOUNT.

493
00:26:34,843 --> 00:26:37,430
NO PHYSIOLOGICAL CHANGES.

494
00:26:37,471 --> 00:26:40,640
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S HIT IT
ON THE HEAD.

495
00:26:42,600 --> 00:26:45,187
SCOTTY...

496
00:26:45,229 --> 00:26:46,730
DID YOU KILL SYBO?

497
00:26:46,772 --> 00:26:48,357
NO, CAPTAIN.

498
00:26:48,399 --> 00:26:49,983
THAT I'M SURE OF.

499
00:26:50,025 --> 00:26:51,944
HE'S BEEN SAYING THAT
RIGHT ALONG.

500
00:26:51,985 --> 00:26:53,820
MEANS NO MORE NOW
THAN IT DID BEFORE.

501
00:26:53,862 --> 00:26:55,864
SCOTTY, LIE TO ME.
HOW OLD ARE YOU?

502
00:26:55,906 --> 00:26:58,534
UH...22, SIR.

503
00:26:58,576 --> 00:27:00,160
INACCURATE. INACCURATE.

504
00:27:00,202 --> 00:27:02,455
DATA IN ERROR.

505
00:27:05,665 --> 00:27:08,294
AFTER THE LIGHTS
WENT OUT, MR. SCOTT,

506
00:27:08,335 --> 00:27:10,963
WHO WAS HOLDING YOUR HAND?

507
00:27:11,004 --> 00:27:13,549
MORLA ON THE ONE SIDE
AND YOU ON THE OTHER, SIR.

508
00:27:13,591 --> 00:27:15,593
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN
ANYTHING, CAPTAIN.

509
00:27:15,633 --> 00:27:17,553
WITH A ROOM THAT SMALL--
THE LIGHTS WERE OUT--

510
00:27:17,595 --> 00:27:19,472
ANYONE WOULD'VE HAD TIME
TO KILL THE LADY.

511
00:27:19,513 --> 00:27:20,931
Hengist:
BUT I REMIND YOU, WE FOUND

512
00:27:20,973 --> 00:27:23,517
MR. SCOTT HOLDING HER IN
HIS ARMS, THE KNIFE ST--

513
00:27:23,559 --> 00:27:25,894
I'M SORRY, SIR,
BUT I MUST.

514
00:27:25,936 --> 00:27:29,064
THE KNIFE STILL IN HER BACK
AND BLOOD ON HIS HANDS.

515
00:27:29,106 --> 00:27:31,649
THE VERIFIER SHOWED THAT
HE WAS TELLING THE TRUTH

516
00:27:31,691 --> 00:27:33,611
WHEN HE SAID
HE DIDN'T KILL HER.

517
00:27:33,651 --> 00:27:35,946
THERE WERE TWO OTHER
WOMEN MURDERED.

518
00:27:38,532 --> 00:27:41,201
MR. SCOTT...

519
00:27:42,953 --> 00:27:44,871
DID YOU KILL KARA?

520
00:27:44,913 --> 00:27:46,499
I DON'T REMEMBER.

521
00:27:46,540 --> 00:27:48,083
DID YOU KILL
LIEUTENANT TRACY?

522
00:27:48,125 --> 00:27:50,836
[SIGHS]
I DON'T REMEMBER.

523
00:27:50,877 --> 00:27:52,421
COMPUTER, ACCURACY SCAN.

524
00:27:52,463 --> 00:27:54,507
SUBJECT RELAYING
ACCURATE ACCOUNT.

525
00:27:54,548 --> 00:27:56,967
NO PHYSIOLOGICAL CHANGES.

526
00:27:57,009 --> 00:27:59,595
ALL THAT PROVES IS THAT
HE'S TELLING THE TRUTH

527
00:27:59,637 --> 00:28:01,180
WHEN HE SAYS
HE DOESN'T REMEMBER.

528
00:28:01,221 --> 00:28:03,182
THIS IS A WASTE OF TIME.

529
00:28:03,223 --> 00:28:04,933
AFTER WE TAKE
THE TESTIMONY HERE,
WE'LL RUN

530
00:28:04,975 --> 00:28:07,685
A PSYCHO-TRICORDER
ANALYSIS OF
MR. SCOTT'S MEMORY,

531
00:28:07,727 --> 00:28:10,439
WHICH IS WHAT WE WANTED
TO DO ON THE SURFACE.

532
00:28:10,481 --> 00:28:12,107
THAT WILL GIVE US
A COMPLETE RECORD.

533
00:28:12,149 --> 00:28:13,651
WILL THAT SATISFY YOU,
MR. HENGIST?

534
00:28:13,691 --> 00:28:16,278
WELL,
IF YOU CAN CONVINCE ME

535
00:28:16,320 --> 00:28:18,364
THAT THE MACHINE
IS INCAPABLE OF ERROR

536
00:28:18,405 --> 00:28:20,658
AND IF IT SHOWS
HE DID NOT KILL THE WOMEN.

537
00:28:20,698 --> 00:28:22,284
THERE WILL BE NO ERROR.

538
00:28:22,326 --> 00:28:23,827
AS FOR THE REST OF IT,

539
00:28:23,869 --> 00:28:25,912
THE READINGS WILL SHOW.

540
00:28:27,206 --> 00:28:29,208
I THINK YOU CAN
STEP DOWN NOW,
MR. SCOTT,

541
00:28:29,249 --> 00:28:30,834
IF THERE ARE
NO OBJECTIONS.

542
00:28:30,876 --> 00:28:32,419
I OBJECT TO THE
ENTIRE PROCEDURE.

543
00:28:32,461 --> 00:28:34,880
MR. HENGIST,
WE ARE HERE ON
MY AUTHORITY.

544
00:28:34,921 --> 00:28:36,798
WE WILL
COOPERATE.

545
00:28:36,840 --> 00:28:39,510
PREFECT,
I KNOW YOU MEAN WELL,
BUT I'VE HAD EXPERIENCE--

546
00:28:39,552 --> 00:28:41,470
FOR THE TIME BEING,
WE WILL ACCEPT

547
00:28:41,512 --> 00:28:43,347
CAPTAIN KIRK'S
EXPLANATION

548
00:28:43,389 --> 00:28:46,392
OF THE MACHINE'S
ACCURACY AS FACTUAL.

549
00:28:46,433 --> 00:28:48,768
I DO, HOWEVER, RESERVE
TO MYSELF THE RIGHT

550
00:28:48,810 --> 00:28:50,479
TO MAKE THE FINAL
DETERMINATION.

551
00:28:50,521 --> 00:28:52,356
WE CAN ASK NO MORE.

552
00:28:52,398 --> 00:28:55,150
MR. MORLA, WILL YOU
TAKE THE STAND?

553
00:29:07,621 --> 00:29:10,165
WHERE WERE YOU AT THE TIME
THAT KARA WAS MURDERED?

554
00:29:10,207 --> 00:29:13,711
I'M NOT SURE.
WALKING HOME, I--I ASSUME.

555
00:29:13,752 --> 00:29:15,629
I WAS ANGRY.

556
00:29:15,671 --> 00:29:18,424
ANGER IS
A RELATIVE STATE, SIR.

557
00:29:18,465 --> 00:29:20,842
WERE YOU ANGRY ENOUGH
TO DO VIOLENCE?

558
00:29:20,884 --> 00:29:22,678
I'VE NEVER DONE VIOLENCE
IN MY LIFE.

559
00:29:22,720 --> 00:29:24,263
I DON'T THINK
THAT I COULD.

560
00:29:24,304 --> 00:29:26,348
YOU'VE GOT TO BELIEVE ME.
I WOULDN'T KILL HER.

561
00:29:26,390 --> 00:29:28,601
I COULDN'T.

562
00:29:28,642 --> 00:29:30,310
I LOVED HER,

563
00:29:30,352 --> 00:29:32,062
AND SHE LOVED ME.

564
00:29:32,104 --> 00:29:33,689
THAT'S NOT TRUE!

565
00:29:33,731 --> 00:29:35,941
HE MIGHT THINK
SHE LOVED HIM,

566
00:29:35,982 --> 00:29:37,984
BUT SHE DIDN'T.

567
00:29:38,026 --> 00:29:39,278
SHE TOLD ME.

568
00:29:39,319 --> 00:29:42,781
HE WAS JEALOUS

569
00:29:42,822 --> 00:29:44,408
ALL THE TIME.

570
00:29:44,450 --> 00:29:47,494
THEY FOUGHT CONSTANTLY.

571
00:29:47,536 --> 00:29:49,288
DID YOU KILL
LIEUTENANT TRACY?

572
00:29:49,329 --> 00:29:50,872
NO.

573
00:29:50,914 --> 00:29:51,915
DID YOU KILL SYBO?

574
00:29:51,957 --> 00:29:53,166
NO.

575
00:29:53,208 --> 00:29:54,752
COMPUTER,
VERIFICATION SCAN.

576
00:29:54,793 --> 00:29:57,170
SUBJECT RELAYING
ACCURATE ACCOUNT,

577
00:29:57,212 --> 00:30:00,173
THOUGH SOME STATEMENTS
SUBJECTIVE.

578
00:30:00,215 --> 00:30:02,301
NO PHYSIOLOGICAL CHANGES.

579
00:30:02,342 --> 00:30:05,971
ALL RIGHT, MR. MORLA,
I THINK YOU CAN
STEP DOWN NOW.

580
00:30:14,313 --> 00:30:17,899
SYBO SPOKE OF A HUNGER
THAT NEVER DIED,

581
00:30:17,941 --> 00:30:20,944
SOMETHING THAT THRIVES
ON...FEAR,

582
00:30:20,986 --> 00:30:23,614
TERROR, DEATH.

583
00:30:23,656 --> 00:30:26,283
MR. SPOCK, MAYBE
WE'RE GOING ABOUT IT
THE WRONG WAY.

584
00:30:26,325 --> 00:30:31,121
LET'S ASSUME THAT SYBO
WAS A SENSITIVE--

585
00:30:31,163 --> 00:30:34,166
THAT SHE DID
SENSE SOMETHING,
SOMETHING EVIL.

586
00:30:34,207 --> 00:30:36,376
SENSITIVITY OF CERTAIN
ARGELIAN WOMEN

587
00:30:36,418 --> 00:30:38,086
IS A DOCUMENTED FACT,
CAPTAIN.

588
00:30:38,128 --> 00:30:41,131
MY POOR SYBO'S TALENT
WAS GENUINE, GENTLEMEN.

589
00:30:41,173 --> 00:30:44,718
WHAT SHE TOLD YOU
WAS TRUE.

590
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:46,136
ALL RIGHT, THEN,

591
00:30:46,178 --> 00:30:48,764
WHAT WAS IT
SHE SAID, EXACTLY?

592
00:30:48,806 --> 00:30:51,266
MONSTROUS EVIL,
ANCIENT TERROR...

593
00:30:51,308 --> 00:30:54,311
THAT DEVOURS
ALL LIFE AND LIGHT.

594
00:30:54,353 --> 00:30:57,397
SHE SAID SOMETHING
ELSE--WORDS THAT
DIDN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

595
00:30:57,439 --> 00:30:59,065
YES.

596
00:30:59,107 --> 00:31:00,651
REDJAC...

597
00:31:00,693 --> 00:31:02,277
BERATIS...

598
00:31:02,319 --> 00:31:05,030
AND, UH...KESLA.

599
00:31:05,071 --> 00:31:08,325
OBSCURE,
MEANINGLESS WORDS.

600
00:31:08,367 --> 00:31:11,328
TO US, PERHAPS,
BUT TO THE COMPUTER?

601
00:31:11,370 --> 00:31:13,955
AH, MR. SPOCK,
CHECK THEM OUT.

602
00:31:13,997 --> 00:31:16,792
COMPUTER,
LINGUISTIC BANK.

603
00:31:16,834 --> 00:31:18,460
DEFINITION
OF FOLLOWING WORD--

604
00:31:18,502 --> 00:31:20,379
REDJAC.

605
00:31:20,420 --> 00:31:22,756
WORKING.

606
00:31:22,798 --> 00:31:24,966
NEGATIVE FINDING.

607
00:31:26,259 --> 00:31:29,888
THERE IS NO SUCH WORD
IN THE LINGUISTICS BANK?

