00:45:37,318 --> 00:45:39,362
BANK AFTER BANK
IS TURNING TO
THE PROBLEM.

921
00:45:39,404 --> 00:45:41,780
IF YOU DRIVE IT OUT OF
THE COMPUTERS, IT'LL JUST
HAVE TO GO SOMEWHERE ELSE.

922
00:45:41,822 --> 00:45:43,282
HOW ARE YOU DOING?

923
00:45:43,324 --> 00:45:45,034
WELL, I'M ALMOST FINISHED--
JUST JARIS AND ME.

924
00:45:45,076 --> 00:45:46,661
[MANIACAL LAUGHTER]

925
00:45:50,665 --> 00:45:52,542
[LAUGHTER FADES]

926
00:45:52,584 --> 00:45:56,795
COMPLETE COMPUTER
CONTROL, CAPTAIN.
THE ENTITY HAS FLED.

927
00:45:56,837 --> 00:45:59,798
YES, BUT WHERE TO?

928
00:45:59,840 --> 00:46:01,758
BONES, WHAT WOULD HAPPEN

929
00:46:01,800 --> 00:46:04,679
IF THAT THING ENTERED
A TRANQUILIZED BODY?

930
00:46:04,721 --> 00:46:07,306
WELL, IT MIGHT TAKE UP
KNITTING, NOTHING MORE
VIOLENT THAN THAT.

931
00:46:07,348 --> 00:46:10,351
AND YOU SAY EVERYONE'S HAD
A SHOT BUT YOU AND JARIS?

932
00:46:10,393 --> 00:46:12,270
AND YOU AND MR. SPOCK,
CAPTAIN.

933
00:46:12,311 --> 00:46:15,565
WELL,
I'M WILLING TO TAKE
A CHANCE ON MR. SPOCK.

934
00:46:15,607 --> 00:46:17,191
BETTER GIVE YOURSELF
A SHOT, DOC.

935
00:46:17,233 --> 00:46:19,277
NO, I DON'T THINK SO.
I THINK I OUGHT
TO STAY CLEAR.

936
00:46:19,318 --> 00:46:21,195
DO AS I SAY.

937
00:46:24,949 --> 00:46:26,909
ALL RIGHT.

938
00:46:26,951 --> 00:46:28,536
[CHUCKLES]

939
00:46:28,578 --> 00:46:30,079
EXTEND YOUR ARM, MR. JARIS.

940
00:46:30,121 --> 00:46:32,789
[HENGIST'S VOICE]
NO, NO, KILL YOU ALL!

941
00:46:32,831 --> 00:46:35,293
DIE! MAKE YOU SUFFER!

942
00:46:39,631 --> 00:46:42,425
EVERYBODY KEEP BACK
OR I'LL KILL HER!

943
00:46:42,467 --> 00:46:44,427
I'LL KILL HER!
KEEP BACK!

944
00:46:44,469 --> 00:46:45,802
McCoy: BETTER BE CAREFUL.

945
00:46:45,844 --> 00:46:47,513
YOU'RE GOING TO HURT
SOMEBODY WITH THAT THING.

946
00:46:47,555 --> 00:46:49,599
OOH! HA HA HA!

947
00:46:51,976 --> 00:46:53,645
YOU'LL SUFFER!
YOU'LL--

948
00:46:53,686 --> 00:46:56,230
SUFF...
HA HA HA HA HA.

949
00:46:56,272 --> 00:46:58,899
I'LL KILL
ALL OF YOU.

950
00:46:58,941 --> 00:47:00,859
LET'S GET HIM TO
THE TRANSPORTER ROOM, QUICK!

951
00:47:00,901 --> 00:47:03,362
[LAUGHING]
YOU'LL...

952
00:47:03,404 --> 00:47:06,157
DIE, DIE, DIE.

953
00:47:06,198 --> 00:47:10,119
EVERYBODY DIE.
HA HA!

954
00:47:10,161 --> 00:47:12,121
[LAUGHING]

955
00:47:12,163 --> 00:47:15,708
KILL, KILL, KILL YOU ALL.

956
00:47:15,750 --> 00:47:16,917
[BEEPS]

957
00:47:16,959 --> 00:47:19,128
DEEP SPACE.
FULL POWER.

958
00:47:19,170 --> 00:47:21,130
WIDEST ANGLE
OF DISPERSION.
MAINTAIN.

959
00:47:21,172 --> 00:47:24,342
NO NEED TO GET EXCITED,
CAPTAIN. I'LL DO IT.

960
00:47:24,383 --> 00:47:26,552
YOU DO IT, SPOCK.

961
00:47:27,844 --> 00:47:31,265
EVERYBODY DIES.
HA HA HA!

962
00:47:31,307 --> 00:47:34,435
YOU WILL
ALL SUFFER.
YOU ALL...

963
00:47:41,359 --> 00:47:45,321
Man: YOU DIDN'T HAVE
TO SHOVE ME, MR. SPOCK.
I'D HAVE GOTTEN ROUND TO IT.

964
00:47:48,032 --> 00:47:49,617
[DOOR SLIDES OPEN]

965
00:47:49,659 --> 00:47:52,203
WELL, JARIS
IS ALL RIGHT. HA HA!

966
00:47:52,244 --> 00:47:55,206
NOW, WHAT DID YOU DO WITH
THAT THING, CAPTAIN, YOU
SEND IT BACK TO THE PLANET?

967
00:47:55,247 --> 00:47:57,874
NO. WE BEAMED IT
OUT INTO OPEN
SPACE, SCOTTY,

968
00:47:57,916 --> 00:47:59,669
WIDEST POSSIBLE
DISPERSION.

969
00:47:59,711 --> 00:48:01,295
THE THING CAN'T DIE.

970
00:48:01,337 --> 00:48:02,921
Spock:
POSSIBLY, DOCTOR.

971
00:48:02,963 --> 00:48:05,174
ITS CONSCIOUSNESS MAY
CONTINUE FOR SOME TIME,

972
00:48:05,216 --> 00:48:07,844
CONSISTING OF BILLIONS
OF SEPARATE BITS OF ENERGY,

973
00:48:07,884 --> 00:48:09,846
FLOATING FOREVER IN SPACE,

974
00:48:09,886 --> 00:48:11,013
POWERLESS.

975
00:48:11,055 --> 00:48:13,683
BUT IT WILL DIE
FINALLY.

976
00:48:13,725 --> 00:48:15,852
YOU SEEM
VERY HAPPY ABOUT
THE WHOLE THING.

977
00:48:15,892 --> 00:48:17,645
WELL, WHY NOT?
FOR A WHILE THERE,

978
00:48:17,687 --> 00:48:19,355
I DIDN'T KNOW WHETHER
I WAS INNOCENT OR GUILTY.

979
00:48:19,397 --> 00:48:21,106
HA HA HA HA!

980
00:48:21,148 --> 00:48:22,483
BONES, HOW LONG
WILL IT TAKE FOR

981
00:48:22,525 --> 00:48:23,984
THIS TRANQUILIZER
TO WEAR OFF?

982
00:48:24,026 --> 00:48:26,738
OH, I DON'T KNOW,
FIVE OR SIX HOURS.

983
00:48:26,779 --> 00:48:29,114
I GAVE HIM A PRETTY
BIG SHOT, JIM.

984
00:48:29,156 --> 00:48:31,450
YES, I CAN SEE THAT.

985
00:48:31,492 --> 00:48:33,411
WELL, MR. SPOCK,
FOR THE NEXT FIVE
OR SIX HOURS,

986
00:48:33,452 --> 00:48:35,413
WE'RE GOING TO HAVE
THE HAPPIEST CREW
IN SPACE.

987
00:48:35,454 --> 00:48:37,164
'COURSE, WE WON'T
GET MUCH WORK DONE.

988
00:48:37,206 --> 00:48:40,334
CAPTAIN, SINCE YOU CAME
TO ARGELIUS TO REST,

989
00:48:40,376 --> 00:48:43,128
I SUGGEST YOU TAKE ADVANTAGE
OF THE OPPORTUNITY.

990
00:48:43,170 --> 00:48:46,131
THAT'S A SPLENDID IDEA,
MR. SPOCK.

991
00:48:46,173 --> 00:48:50,094
I KNOW A CAFE
WHERE THE WOMEN ARE SO--

992
00:48:50,135 --> 00:48:51,095
I KNOW THE PLACE, JIM.

993
00:48:51,136 --> 00:48:52,513
LET'S GO SEE!

994
00:48:52,555 --> 00:48:53,765
YOU GENTLEMEN,
IN YOUR CONDITION?

995
00:48:53,806 --> 00:48:55,391
DON'T BE RIDICULOUS.

996
00:48:55,433 --> 00:48:58,770
MR. SPOCK, THIS CAFE
HAS WOMEN THAT ARE SO...

997
00:49:04,859 --> 00:49:07,319
NO, I GUESS NOT.

998
00:49:08,863 --> 00:49:10,907
ALONE?

999
00:49:16,495 --> 00:49:19,081
GENTLEMEN...

1000
00:49:19,123 --> 00:49:21,166
[LAUGHING]
